    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON EFA-12 - INSPECT - KNUCKLE VERTICAL PLAY INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0200601" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="2">
        <title>KNUCKLE VERTICAL PLAY INSPECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on axle beam. Reference the knuckle cap (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200610">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200610.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Reference the Dial Indicator</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pry steering knuckle downward (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200611">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200611.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Pry Knuckle Downward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the front axle to obtain dial indicator reading. If reading exceeds 0.040 inch (1.02
                mm), inspect thrust bearings. Replace if necessary and adjust. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02006_6.xml" xrefid="hl0200603">STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</hotlnk>
                for overhaul procedures
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspection procedures above assume axle is assembled and installed in vehicle with tire and
                        wheels. Checking knuckle vertical play during axle assembly requires different procedure. Refer
                        to
                        <hotlnk document="s02006_21.xml" xrefid="hl0200604">STEERING KNUCKLE ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
